praeterquam propinquorum suorum hereditates: the meaning is not clear. Perhaps Theophanes had married into the family of Balbus, and Balbus, by being Theophanes' heir, only inherited the property of his own relations. Perhaps we are supposed to under- stand that the money received by Balbus through Theophanes originally belonged to Balbus’ own family.

The prosecutor tries to bring odium on Balbus by referring to five things, viz.: (l) his wealth, (2) his luxury, (3) his Tusculan estate, (4) his entry into the Clustumine tribe, and (5) his adoption by Theophanes.
